description.en:
Modification of a physical object that changes it in a voluntary and controlled way. This includes experiments and conservation activities that physically modify the object in some way. Modification is voluntary and controlled. For example, changing an illumination color.

Original:  Rob Sanderson (https://github.com/archesproject/arches-for-science/blob/master/afs/pkg/graphs/resource_models/Modification.json) from Linked Art Project.

subtitle.en: A modification to a physical object that changes but does not destroy it
